Description: Scarab carved from stone; underside incised with two outward facing Maat feathers below a sun-disc; motif surrounded by a single incised line.
Curator's comments: Scarab not yet located, published by Petrie (Petrie 1886, pl. XXXVIII, no. 193). Petrie, W.M.F. 1886, Naukratis. Part I, 1884–5 (Third Memoir of the Egypt Exploration Fund), London.
